*  1) The illegal, but rare, practice of kidnapping infants, presumably for the purpose of selling the child on a black market, either within the national borders, or (more commonly) internationally.  Baby-snatching is the subject of an intense, largely paranoid fear among indigenous populations in Latin America, from Mexico to Boliva.
*  2) (Obs)Stealing the heart (too oft metonymous for virginity) of a noticeablly younger member of the opposite sex; or the same sex, for that matter.